# GitHub push for FYP HANSON

After making any code changes in `FYP HANSON`, push to GitHub unless the user says not to:

1. Run from project root:
   ```
   git add -A
   git status
   git commit -m "<short descriptive message>"
   git push origin main
   ```
2. Remote: `https://github.com/hansongnkk01/fyp-hanson.git` branch `main`
3. Do NOT commit `esp32-master/config.h` (WiFi secrets — gitignored)
4. DO commit `website/config.js` when Supabase settings change (needed for Vercel)
5. Briefly tell the user the push succeeded and Vercel will auto-redeploy

Alternative: run `.\push-to-github.ps1 "commit message"` in the project folder.
